# Huntarr — Rules Index

Development rules are split into focused files for Cursor. This index is always applied; others apply by glob or when relevant.

| File | Purpose |
|------|--------|
| **huntarr-critical.mdc** | No auto-commit, testing, deploy, version, cross-platform (alwaysApply) |
| **huntarr-database.mdc** | DatabaseManager only; no SQLite/JSON; paths; Synology |
| **huntarr-frontend.mdc** | Relative URLs, BASE_URL frontend, docs links, JS, refresh, sidebars, CSS |
| **huntarr-base-url.mdc** | Backend BASE_URL: middleware, redirects, path checks |
| **huntarr-bug-patterns.mdc** | Known bug patterns and fixes (auth, settings, Lidarr, Hunt Manager, etc.) |
| **huntarr-scan-debug.mdc** | Key files, violation scan commands, debugging tips |
| **confirm-modals.mdc** | HuntarrConfirm for destructive/critical actions |
| **unraid-always-redeploy.mdc** | Deploy to Unraid after code changes; use deploy-with-build.exp |

After code changes: run Unraid deploy (`./unraid/deploy-with-build.exp`) or local Docker build per huntarr-critical.mdc.
